1.00	Lisa_Lowe	Lisa Lowe	Lisa Lowe is a professor of comparative literature at the University of California, San Diego and a noted scholar in the fields of comparative literature, American studies, Asian American studies and the cultural politics of colonialism and migration. She was Visiting Professor of American Studies at Yale University in 2007-2008. In 2011-2012, she is a University of California President's Faculty Research Fellow and Visiting Fellow at the School of Advanced Study, University of London.	
